{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/development-environments","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"lando\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lando\" aria-label=\"lando permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lando</h1>\n<p>Lando provides docker-based development environments that integrate with Drupal sites hosted on Pantheon using a terminus cli. You can easily pull the database and files directory from a live site using \"lando pull\" or import a downloaded database with \"db-import. Lando runs much faster on linux PCs as opposed to Macs due to how docker uses the filesystem. Provided your hardware can support support the memory footprint of docker containers, lando is a much more configurable solution than using MAMP or a native LAMP stack.</p>\n<h2 id=\"using-lando-on-a-new-site\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#using-lando-on-a-new-site\" aria-label=\"using lando on a new site permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Using Lando on a new site</h2>\n<ol start=\"0\">\n<li>in an empty directory <code class=\"language-text\">lando init</code></li>\n<li>enter name, recipe etc.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">lando start</code></li>\n<li>get codebase by whatever method</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">lando info</code> to get URLs of local site</li>\n<li>go to install page and enter credentials from <code class=\"language-text\">lando info</code>  output</li>\n<li>install as you normally would</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"using-lando-on-existing-site\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#using-lando-on-existing-site\" aria-label=\"using lando on existing site permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Using Lando on existing site</h2>\n<ol start=\"0\">\n<li>in site root <code class=\"language-text\">lando init</code></li>\n<li>enter name, recipe etc</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">lando start</code></li>\n<li>import db with <code class=\"language-text\">lando db-import mydb.sql</code></li>\n<li>download files manually and place in /sites/default/files</li>\n<li>\n<p>add the following snippet to local-settings.php so site will use the lando database</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$lando_info = json_decode(getenv('LANDO_INFO'), TRUE);\n$databases['default']['default'] = array(\n'driver' => 'mysql',\n'database' => $lando_info['database']['creds']['database'],\n'username' => $lando_info['database']['creds']['user'],\n'password' => $lando_info['database']['creds']['password'],\n'host' => $lando_info['database']['internal_connection']['host'],\n'prefix' => '',\n);</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">lando info</code> for URL and you should be ready</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"custom-lando-commands\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#custom-lando-commands\" aria-label=\"custom lando commands permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Custom Lando commands</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">tooling:\n  cr:\n    service: appserver\n    description: Clear the drupal cache\n    cmd:\n      - /app/scripts/d8-lando-cache-clear.sh</code></pre></div>\n<p>Preface the path to the script with \"app\" so the command can be run from anywhere in the filesystem</p>\n<h2 id=\"add-phpmyadmin\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#add-phpmyadmin\" aria-label=\"add phpmyadmin permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Add phpmyadmin</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">services:\n  pma:\n    type: phpmyadmin\n    hosts:\n      - database</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"date":"2018-8-30","path":"/blog/development-environments","title":"dev environments","author":"Mike Marsello","template":"blog","desc":"development environments"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}